message.content: cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.AI. The paper discusses a text visualization technique that aids visual analysis of documents by referencing a domain ontology to represent the conceptual relationships in a document. The examples used to demonstrate the technique are research articles and transcripts of technical presentations in the computer science domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to sub-categories related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), deep learning (cs.DL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
